text: Moneymore is a village in Northern Ireland, in the United Kingdom. It is from Cookstown and from Magherafelt. ==Population facts== On 29 April 2001 the United Kingdom government had a census and saw that there were 1,369 people living in Moneymore. They also saw that: *25.0% of the people were under 16 years old and 16.1% were over 60 years old. *47.9% of the people were male and 52.1% were female. *47.8% of the people were from a Roman Catholic background and 51.0% were from a Protestant background; *3.1% of people aged 16â€“74 had no job.NI Neighbourhood Information Service ==References== Category:Villages in Northern Ireland
